The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to neuroimaging data for the prediction of Alzheimer's Disease. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the proposed model on healthcare practitioners, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
